events.pleaseNote: Souper-spectacle Chaque soir d'événement, Le Balcon propose un délicieux menu saisonnier. La table d'hôte comprend deux choix d'entrée, trois choix de plat principal et un délice sucré. Le Balcon propose une carte de vins internationale majoritairement composée d'importations privées. La carte des cocktails revisite les classiques, en y infusant des saveurs italiennes, sud-américaines et antillaises. Dinner-Show Every show night, Le Balcon serves a delicious seasonal menu. The table d'hôte includes your choice of two appetizers and three mains, followed by a scrumptious dessert. To accompany your meal Le Balcon's international wine list features many fine private imports, while the cocktail list revisits the classics with an Italian, South American or Caribbean twist.

venues.parkingDetail: Our venue uses a dispersed parking model which means that event-goers are encouraged to use public and private parking lots as well as on-street options throughout the downtown core. There are over 8,675 parking (combined public/private) spaces in Downtown Moncton. Within a maximum walk time of 14 minutes, there are approximately 3,300 off-street parking lot spaces available after 6pm. There are countless options for you to choose from that include both low cost and free options. To plan the option that is best for you, go to www.mybestoption.ca
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: The arena is fully accessible. All accessible seating is available through your local Ticketmaster location, Charge-by-Phone or the Avenir Centre Box Office. Patrons with disabilities may also go directly to the Avenir Centre Box Office to purchase their tickets. When arriving at the Avenir Centre please use the accessible drop off zone and make your way to Gate 6 where our event centre staff can guide you to your designated seat. Accessibility areas are located at the top of sections 102 to 107. Please note that there is no wheelchair or disability seating permitted on the floor, due to safety reasons. If you have a disability and purchased a ticket in error on the floor, the venue reserves the right to relocate you.

generalInfo.generalRule: Food and drink concessions are located throughout the venue. No outside food or beverage will be permitted to enter the facility. Re-Entry to the venue is not permitted. Exceptions can be made in emergency or medical situations.

events.name: C'est si bon ... de danser!
events.info: L'émission radiophonique à succès C'EST SI BON, diffusée sur ICI MUSIQUE et animée par Claude Saucier, se transporte sur scène avec le spectacle dansant à grand déploiement C'EST SI BON... DE DANSER! Pour ce rendez-vous unique, Claude Saucier assure l'animation et sera rejoint sur scène par les interprètes Kim Richardson ou Sylvie DesGroseilliers, et Marc Hervieux. Un grand orchestre de 18 musiciens sous la direction de Ron Di Lauro vous fera revivre les inoubliables mélodies des soirées musicales des années 40 et 50 et l'ambiance des ballrooms. Tous seront unis afin de refléter l'esprit du filon musical de la populaire émission radiophonique C'EST SI BON.

boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: • Les soirs de spectacle, la billetterie est ouverte jusqu'à 21 h. • Les billets achetés par téléphone et internet peuvent être récupérés au guichet du MTELUS durant les heures d'ouverture. Il est d'ailleurs fortement recommandé de récupérer les billets à l'avance afin d'éviter la file d'attente au guichet les soirs de spectacle. • Des frais d'administration de 2.00$ vous seront facturés si vous effectuez vos transactions à la billetterie de L'Astral ou au guichet du MTELUS. • The box office is open until 9 p.m. on the night of a performance. • Tickets purchased by phone or internet can be picked up at the MTELUS box office during opening hours. We highly recommend that you pick up tickets in advance to avoid waiting in line at the box office the night of a show. • A service fee of $2.00 will be charged for transactions at the box office of L'Astral and MMTELUS.

generalInfo.generalRule: All tickets are final sale, no refunds or exchanges. Our venue has gone cashless, we will only accept debit, credit, and gift cards on site. We require all guests (12 years and older) and event staff of indoor and outdoor ticketed events to be fully vaccinated, which requires that 14 days have passed since your final dose.
generalInfo.childRule: For our regular sporting events, children 2 years of age and under may enter without a ticket but must sit on the lap of an accompanying adult. Please note: Some shows (especially those intended for children) will have a different age policy. Please see the specific event page or contact the ticket office at boxoffice@tdplace.ca.
